        <title>Adding the Linear String Graphic Organizer</title>
        <contents>&lt;table style="width: 50%;" align="right" border="0" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="5"&gt;
&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td style="border-color: #000000; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px;"&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;____________________________&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;↓&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td style="border-color: #000000; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px;"&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;_____________________________&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;_&lt;span style="text-decoration: underline;"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Helps her sister with homework&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;___&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;_____________________________&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;___&lt;span style="text-decoration: underline;"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Cleans the house&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;_____________&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;↓&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td style="border-color: #000000; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px;"&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;_____________________________&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;This simple modification gives learners practice with . . .&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Organizing information&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Categorizing information&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Sequencing&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Recognizing a chronology&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Listen to audio:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="@@PLUGINFILE@@/ELL_MOD1_UNIT4_0140.mp3"&gt;ELL_MOD1_UNIT4_0140.mp3&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;details&gt;&lt;summary&gt;Audio transcript&lt;/summary&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you chose all four skills, you were right! With this first modification, reading and filling in a linear string graphic organizer, learners practice organizing and categorizing information, and sequencing events. The linear string provides a visual representation of the chronology of Choua’s day. Notice that information in the last box is actually in the first paragraph. The linear string makes that more apparent to the learner. Compare this reading task to the original task of reading and answering comprehension questions. See how this simple modification gives beginners practice with critical thinking. At this level, we don’t have to name these skills; we are simply teaching in a way that gives learners practice with them. We have moved from Level 1 Depth of Knowledge to Level 2 and beyond already, haven’t we?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/details&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</contents>
