        <title>Video: Tasks that promote critical thinking</title>
        <contents>&lt;p style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;This video demonstrates how the choice of tasks we give learners, whether in a grammar, vocabulary, listening, speaking or writing lesson, can add a layer of critical thinking at any level of instruction.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;&lt;object width="560" height="315"&gt;&lt;param name="movie" value="//www.youtube.com/embed/6NSXospk9Js?hl=en_US&amp;amp;version=3&amp;amp;rel=0" /&gt;&lt;param name="allowFullScreen" value="true" /&gt;&lt;param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always" /&gt;&lt;embed height="315" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="560" src="https://www.youtube.com/v/6NSXospk9Js?hl=en_US&amp;amp;version=3&amp;amp;rel=0" allowfullscreen="true" allowscriptaccess="always" title="Adobe Flash Player" /&gt;&lt;/object&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Task&lt;/strong&gt;: Print the &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a title="Video Observation Form" href="@@PLUGINFILE@@/M1U4_S39_Video_Obs_508.docx" target="_blank"&gt;Video Observation Form&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; and note the task type and the thinking skills practiced with each. The video also demonstrates valuable "learning" skills that relate to critical thinking, for example, categorizing information to help with memory retention.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Task for Instructors&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Categories presented in the video:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol style="text-align: left;"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Categorizing tasks&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Activities using grids&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Graphic organizers&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Choose three ideas from the video, one from each category presented, that you could readily apply to a lesson you commonly teach. &lt;strong&gt;What critical thinking skills would this add to your lesson? What Depth of Knowledge level would you reach and why? Present these ideas to colleagues if you are working with others on this unit.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;1. Idea 1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;2. Idea 2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;3. Idea 3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
