&lt;td style="text-align: center;"&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration: underline;"&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;↓&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td style="border-color: #000000; border-style: solid; border-width: 1px;"&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="text-decoration: underline;"&gt;&lt;em&gt;__Goes to school________________&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Also provides practice with . . .&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Reading for specific information&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Finding evidence to support a claim&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Information transfer—text to visual representation&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Note-taking (linear string serving as a precursor to note-taking)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Listen to audio:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="@@PLUGINFILE@@/ELL_MOD1_UNIT4_0150.mp3"&gt;ELL_MOD1_UNIT4_0150.mp3&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;details&gt;&lt;summary&gt;Audio transcript&lt;/summary&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This approach includes additional benefits, such as reading for specific information, information transfer (text to visual representations), and note-taking, which are explored in depth in Unit 3 of this module. These are all important academic and work skills. This task also makes evidence to support a claim more obvious. The text says Choua likes her new schedule. Why? The word “now” is a good clue as it tells us something changed in Choua’s life. Now let’s turn to the next modification where students are given a card with just one activity in Choua’s day and asked to line up according to morning, afternoon or evening activities, a sort of human graphic organizer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/details&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</contents>
        <contentsformat>1</contentsformat>
